<h2><font face="Verdana" color="Navy">Camp Staff</font></h2>

<p>Our staff is trained with over 50 hours of camp preparation including Child Sexual Abuse Prevention, Emergency Drills, Basic First Aid and CPR Certification, Multi-cultural awareness, Child Development, Team-building, and other workshops, in preparation for working with children.</p>
<p>A Registered Nurse or Nurse Practitioner is on duty during all camp sessions.</p>
<p>Our waterfront staff is Red Cross certified in lifesaving, CPR and First Aid.  A lifeguard will be on duty at all times that campers are in or near the water.</p>
<p>Our summer camp staff brings a variety of gifts, talents, and camp experiences to their work.  Our programs will promote creativity and spiritual growth in addition to recreation.  The camp staff is motivated by a sincere belief in the importance of our children and young people and in programming to meet their needs and expectations.</p>

